item.title: 217. Contains Duplicate
item.description: The Problem Statement This problem is taken from LeetCode. First Solution: std::unordered_set In order to avoid quadratic time complexity resulting from comparing each pair of numbers, we can use a std::unordered_set<int>. We iterate once through all elements and check if the element in already in our set.
